21/04/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis said Tuesday (20 April) that Greece would strongly back Turkey's EU membership efforts. The message of support came as Karamanlis and his Turkish counterpart, Recep Tayyip Erdogan, prepared to attend the Southeast European Countries' Co-operation Process summit in Sarajevo, which begins Wednesday. The two leaders will meet during the summit.
In other news, a new poll published Monday in the Belgian newspaper <I>De Standaard</I> suggests that seven out of 10 Belgian citizens believe Turkey should be allowed to join the EU if it meets all membership criteria. About 75 per cent said the EU should be open to a Muslim country within its ranks. (ANA, MPA, Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, NTV - 20/04/04; De Standaard - 19/04/04)
